Nginx/TP5 setup:

mkdir $HOME/nginx/
pushd $HOME/nginx/
wget http://nginx.org/download/nginx-1.2.3.tar.gz
tar xzf nginx-1.2.3.tar.gz
cd nginx-1.2.3
./configure --prefix=$HOME/nginx/install --without-http-rewrite-module  # without HTTP rewrite module because I didn't have PCRE installed and didn't want to bother
make
make install
cd ../install/conf
vim nginx.conf # edit the "listen 80;" to be "listen 8001; listen 8002; ... listen 8100;"
cd ../html/
wget http://build.mozilla.org/talos/zips/tp5.zip
unzip tp5.zip
cd ../sbin
./nginx
popd

Build other pieces:

./build.sh

Device port forwarding setup:

adb push forwarder/device-forwarder.jar /sdcard/
adb forward tcp:8000 tcp:8000
adb shell
-> su
-> dalvikvm -cp /sdcard/device-forwarder.jar Main -device 8000  # this will block
java -cp forwarder/host-forwarder.jar Main -host 8000 10    # this will block

Fennec addon (mozmill replacement) setup:

adb push fennec-addon-awsy/awsy.xpi /sdcard/
# start fennec, load /sdcard/ and click on awsy.xpi, install the addon
# then quit fennec and make a backup of the clean profile
adb shell
-> su
-> cd /data/data/org.mozilla.fennec_$USER
-> tar czf /sdcard/profile.tgz *

Fennec profile reset:

adb shell
-> su
-> cd /data/data/org.mozilla.fennec_$USER
-> rm -r *
-> tar xzf /sdcard/profile.tgz
